Pfizer made nearly $37bn (¬£27bn) in sales from its Covid-19 vaccine last year ‚Äì making it one of the most lucrative products in history ‚Äì and has forecast another bumper year in 2022, with a big boost coming from its Covid-19 pill Paxlovid.

The bumper sales prompted accusations from campaigners of ‚Äúpandemic profiteering‚Äù. The group Global Justice Now said the annual revenue of $81bn was more than the GDP of most countries and accused Pfizer of ‚Äúripping off public health systems‚Äù.

The US drugmaker‚Äôs overall revenues in 2021 doubled to $81.3bn, and it expects to make record revenues of $98bn to $102bn this year.

The drugmaker made a net profit of nearly $22bn last year, up from $9.1bn in 2020. It increased its 2022 estimate for Comirnaty sales to $32bn and expects Paxlovid to contribute $22bn in revenues.

Pfizer made nearly $37bn (¬£27bn) in sales from its Covid-19 vaccine last year ‚Äì making it one of the most lucrative products in history ‚Äì and has forecast another bumper year in 2022, with a big boost coming from its Covid-19 pill Paxlovid.

The bumper sales prompted accusations from campaigners of ‚Äúpandemic profiteering‚Äù. The group Global Justice Now said the annual revenue of $81bn was more than the GDP of most countries and accused Pfizer of ‚Äúripping off public health systems‚Äù.

The US drugmaker‚Äôs overall revenues in 2021 doubled to $81.3bn, and it expects to make record revenues of $98bn to $102bn this year.

The drugmaker made a net profit of nearly $22bn last year, up from $9.1bn in 2020. It increased its 2022 estimate for Comirnaty sales to $32bn and expects Paxlovid to contribute $22bn in revenues.
